T1  - A disaster explanation of equity term structures
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfaf034
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 29
IS  - 5
SP  - 1437
EP  - 1465
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This article extends the rare disaster framework by introducing a model with a time‐varying disaster recovery feature. The model yields closed‐form pricing formulas for stocks and dividend strips. Calibrated using international disaster data, it quantitatively captures both the unconditional and conditional term structures of equity risk premia. It replicates key empirical patterns, including a downward-sloping unconditional term structure of one-period returns and a countercyclical conditional slope, and generates novel predictions for capital asset pricing model beta, alpha, and price.
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfaf034
ER  - 




